1
00:00:05,423 --> 00:00:09,147
Everyone wants divinity
to be within

2
00:00:09,147 --> 00:00:13,116
the realm of human comprehension,
human feasibility;

3
00:00:13,116 --> 00:00:16,320
what we think 
is possible rationally.

4
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:20,888
That’s why people
are not interested in God,

5
00:00:20,888 --> 00:00:22,984
or want little 
or nothing to do with it.

6
00:00:23,091 --> 00:00:26,959
[Inconceivable but Perceivable]

7
00:00:26,959 --> 00:00:30,591
Acintya-śakti, muhyanti yat sūrayaḥ;

8
00:00:30,792 --> 00:00:33,528
The God, the Kṛṣṇa
we’re interested in

9
00:00:33,528 --> 00:00:37,254
is bewildering 
even to the demigods,

10
00:00:37,254 --> 00:00:43,434
can bewilder Brahmā,
Indra, Śiva.

11
00:00:44,460 --> 00:00:49,797
Mahā-Viṣṇu wants 
a glimpse of Kṛṣṇa;

12
00:00:49,797 --> 00:00:52,644
wants to see
the beauty of Kṛṣṇa,

13
00:00:52,644 --> 00:00:55,748
how beautiful He must be.

14
00:00:55,781 --> 00:01:00,455
Even other forms of Kṛṣṇa
want to see, have a glimpse.

15
00:01:00,514 --> 00:01:05,099
Yaḿ śyāmasundaram
acintya-guṇa-svarūpaḿ 
[Bs: 5.38].

16
00:01:05,509 --> 00:01:10,394
He says, Śyāmasundar, Kṛṣṇa,
what does he look like?

17
00:01:10,394 --> 00:01:12,355
Acintya-guṇa-svarūp.

18
00:01:12,355 --> 00:01:18,289
This svarūp, this form,
has inconceivable qualities.

19
00:01:18,499 --> 00:01:20,691
People say,
“Why is Kṛṣṇa this colour?

20
00:01:20,691 --> 00:01:22,036
Why is he like that?”

21
00:01:22,036 --> 00:01:27,425
It’s an inconceivable colour;
an inconceivable form.

22
00:01:27,601 --> 00:01:30,899
But we’re given some hints,
local references.

23
00:01:32,308 --> 00:01:41,011
Dvārakā Kṛṣṇa is enamoured
by the beauty of Vṛndāvan Kṛṣṇa,

24
00:01:45,332 --> 00:01:47,906
and in the inverse.

25
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:51,230
See, these things become
more meaningful

26
00:01:51,230 --> 00:01:54,903
the more we become
acquainted with them.

27
00:01:55,286 --> 00:01:58,982
So if we understand
how inconceivably beautiful

28
00:01:59,012 --> 00:02:02,029
and attractive Viṣṇu is,

29
00:02:02,075 --> 00:02:07,818
then this will take on
increased connotation,

30
00:02:07,829 --> 00:02:11,073
and meaning
when we hear that

31
00:02:11,073 --> 00:02:14,916
when the Vraja-gopīs
are searching for Kṛṣṇa

32
00:02:14,916 --> 00:02:21,089
and they think they see Him hiding
in a kuñj, the kuñja, because He is,

33
00:02:21,089 --> 00:02:24,039
and as they think they’ve found Him
and they’re running towards Him,

34
00:02:24,039 --> 00:02:28,556
Kṛṣṇa pushes out two more arms
and takes a Viṣṇu form.

35
00:02:28,556 --> 00:02:31,252
And when the Vraja-gopīs
encounter him and see,

36
00:02:31,252 --> 00:02:34,951
from a distance it looked like Kṛṣṇa
but close up it’s Viṣṇu,

37
00:02:34,951 --> 00:02:37,328
it says,
“rāgodayaḥ kuñcati” 
[Cc: 1.17.281];

38
00:02:37,328 --> 00:02:43,261
their hearts are …
well one word is crippled,

39
00:02:43,261 --> 00:02:47,253
but … they’re disappointed.

40
00:02:47,253 --> 00:02:54,372
“Oh, Namo Nārāyaṇa,” they’re respectful,
“have you seen Kṛṣṇa?
 

41
00:02:54,372 --> 00:02:56,482
We’re searching for Kṛṣṇa,

42
00:02:56,482 --> 00:03:01,251
and you know everything,
where’s He hiding?”

43
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:08,595
And so that shows something,
that Vraja-gopīs

44
00:03:08,595 --> 00:03:15,274
are dismissing Viṣṇu
from the object of their search.

45
00:03:16,236 --> 00:03:19,611
Progress means elimination
and a new acceptance.

46
00:03:19,611 --> 00:03:21,898
Raghunāth Dās Goswāmī says,

47
00:03:21,898 --> 00:03:25,840
“Don’t be too attentive
to vidhi-mārga,

48
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:30,876
because if you are
you’ll be hurled down to Vaikuṇṭha.”

49
00:03:31,646 --> 00:03:34,208
Raghunāth Dās Goswāmī,
the prayojan tattva ācārya,

50
00:03:34,208 --> 00:03:36,377
can say such a thing.

51
00:03:37,841 --> 00:03:44,362
So, Vraja-gopīs, they dismiss Viṣṇu
from the object of their search.

52
00:03:44,735 --> 00:03:46,941
Is He not the Absolute Truth?

53
00:03:46,941 --> 00:03:50,485
Is He not Bhagavān?

54
00:03:50,887 --> 00:03:53,455
Dismissed.

55
00:03:53,799 --> 00:03:55,890
Not interested.

56
00:03:56,005 --> 00:03:58,891
Hearts are disappointed.

57
00:03:59,129 --> 00:04:02,745
Then what is it
they’re looking for

58
00:04:04,283 --> 00:04:10,475
that Viṣṇu cannot reciprocate?

59
00:04:11,318 --> 00:04:16,830
Therefore Kṛṣṇa’s called
Akhila-rasāmṛta-mūrti,

60
00:04:16,935 --> 00:04:21,369
He’s the all-accommodating,
all-reciprocating:

61
00:04:21,369 --> 00:04:23,311
Rasa-mūrtimān.

62
00:04:23,696 --> 00:04:31,445
So we shall resist trying to take the infinite, 
the Supreme Absolute Truth,

63
00:04:31,445 --> 00:04:40,223
and make a tree chart, or want
every little aspect of the Infinite

64
00:04:40,223 --> 00:04:46,651
to fit in a little box 
in our puppy brain;

65
00:04:48,114 --> 00:04:52,094
our skull size kingdoms 
that we rule over.

